# TypeScript Conventions

- Keep client/server contracts explicit with shared request/response shapes at route boundaries.
- In server code, type route params/body/query and DB row mappings instead of relying on implicit `any`.
- In client code, type API fetch results before rendering and avoid untyped object indexing.
- Prefer existing project patterns and naming in nearby files over introducing new abstractions.
